<span id="freeTextContainer3692903346063157913">Based on its title and it having been named by the Royal Institution of Great Britain as &quot;the best science book ever,&quot; I thought this would be a science book. But it&apos;s not. It is something of a memoir, told in short stories, about an Italian chemist (who happens to be Jewish) navigating the late 1930s and early to mid 1940s. Through each short story Mr. Levi brings to life one of the elements of the periodic table. It&apos;s an excellent, entertaining book. </span>
  <span id="freeText3692903346063157913" style="display:none">Based on its title and it having been named by the Royal Institution of Great Britain as "the best science book ever," I thought this would be a science book. But it's not. It is something of a memoir, told in short stories, about an Italian chemist (who happens to be Jewish) navigating the late 1930s and early to mid 1940s. Through each short story Mr. Levi brings to life one of the elements of the periodic table. It's an excellent, entertaining book. </span>
